HEADWORD: Indecomposable
<hw>In*de`com*pos"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>decomposable</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ind⟦eacute⟧composable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not decomposable;
incapable or difficult of decomposition; not resolvable into its
constituents or elements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indecomposableness</ent>⟦br⟧
